Wild dogs are a vicious, aggressive form of the domesticated dog that can be found in the Brimhaven Dungeon, except in the iron and steel dragon areas. They are generally considered a pest by low-levelled players due to their tendency to attack and pile them while they are fighting other monsters, but are of minimal threat to higher-levelled players. They are aggressive to players below combat level 75, though their aggression is usually not an issue, since most players capable of accessing the dungeon will generally have sufficient combat experience to make them tolerant.

They can also be killed for a dog slayer task.

With Karamja gloves 4, players can deal double damage against Wild dogs. However, this perk is essentially useless given the elite task set's requirements.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Prior to an unknown update in 2021 wild dogs dropped Summoning charms, with a relatively high green charm drop rate. Following that update wild dogs drop no charms and are classified as a free-to-play monster despite only appearing in a pay-to-play area.
